            {
              "id": "CVE-2019-9936-sqlite-libs",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2019-9936 low vulnerability for sqlite-libs package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A vulnerability was found in SQLite, where a heap-based buffer over-read occurs in the fts5HashEntrySort function within sqlite3.c, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability by running specially crafted queries, lead to an information leak."
