            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-45447-openssl",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-45447 high vulnerability for openssl package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in OpenSSL. When processing a specially crafted PKCS#7 or S/MIME (Secure/Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions) signed message, a heap use-after-free vulnerability in the PKCS7_verify() function can be triggered. This occurs if the SignedData digestAlgorithms field is present as an empty ASN.1 SET, leading to incorrect memory deallocation. A remote attacker could exploit this to cause application crashes, memory corruption, or potentially achieve remote code execution."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-45447",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-45447\nSeverity: high\nPackage: openssl\nVersion: 1:1.1.1k-15.el8_10\nFix Version: 1:1.1.1k-16.el8_6\nType: rpm\nLocation: /var/lib/rpm/Packages\nData Namespace: redhat:distro:redhat:8\nLink: [CVE-2026-45447](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-45447)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-45447**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | openssl  | 1:1.1.1k-15.el8_10  | 1:1.1.1k-16.el8_6  | rpm  | /var/lib/rpm/Packages  | redhat:distro:redhat:8  | [CVE-2026-45447](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-45447)  |\n"
