            {
              "id": "CVE-2024-41996-openssl",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2024-41996 low vulnerability for openssl package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A vulnerability was found in the Diffie-Hellman Ephemeral (DHE) Key Agreement Protocol, where a malicious client can exploit the server's public key validation process. By forcing the server to use DHE and validating the order of public keys, the client can trigger expensive server-side modular exponentiation calculations. This issue results in asymmetric resource consumption, potentially leading to a denial of service (DoS) attack by overwhelming the server with computationally intensive operations."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-41996",
              "help": {
