              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-32778 medium vulnerability for expat package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in libexpat. This vulnerability allows an attacker to trigger a NULL pointer dereference in the `setContext` function. This occurs when the system attempts to retry an operation after an out-of-memory condition, which can lead to a Denial of Service (DoS) for the affected application."
              },
