              "id": "CVE-2026-42250-bzip2-libs",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-42250 medium vulnerability for bzip2-libs package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in bzip2. The bzip2recover utility contains an off-by-one error that allows a local attacker to cause an out-of-bounds write to a global buffer by processing a specially crafted file. This memory corruption can lead to a crash, resulting in a Denial of Service (DoS)."
