              "id": "CVE-2026-41990-libgcrypt",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-41990 low vulnerability for libgcrypt package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in Libgcrypt. During Dilithium signing operations, the library fails to perform a bounds check when writing to a static array. While the data involved is not directly controlled by an attacker, this vulnerability could lead to memory corruption, potentially resulting in a denial of service (DoS) or affecting data integrity."
