            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-24515-expat",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-24515 low vulnerability for expat package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A null pointer dereference flaw has been discovered in libexpat. The function `XML_ExternalEntityParserCreate` failed to copy the encoding handler data passed to XML_SetUnknownEncodingHandler from the parent to the new subparser. This can cause a NULL dereference from external entities that declare use of an unknown encoding. The expected impact is denial of service. It takes use of both functions `XML_ExternalEntityParserCreate` and `XML_SetUnknownEncodingHandler` for an application to be vulnerable."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-24515",
              "help": {
