            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-1485-glib2",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-1485 low vulnerability for glib2 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in Glib's content type parsing logic. This buffer underflow vulnerability occurs because the length of a header line is stored in a signed integer, which can lead to integer wraparound for very large inputs. This results in pointer underflow and out-of-bounds memory access. Exploitation requires a local user to install or process a specially crafted treemagic file, which can lead to local denial of service or application instability."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-1485",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-1485\nSeverity: low\nPackage: glib2\nVersion: 2.56.4-168.el8_10\nFix Version: \nType: rpm\nLocation: /var/lib/rpm/Packages\nData Namespace: redhat:distro:redhat:8\nLink: [CVE-2026-1485](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-1485)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-1485**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| low  | glib2  | 2.56.4-168.el8_10  |   | rpm  | /var/lib/rpm/Packages  | redhat:distro:redhat:8  | [CVE-2026-1485](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2026-1485)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:rpm/rocky/glib2@2.56.4-168.el8_10?arch=x86_64\u0026distro=rocky-8.10\u0026upstream=glib2-2.56.4-168.el8_10.src.rpm"
                ],
